1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper introduces a new modulation technique (OTFS) and discusses its benefits in high-Doppler fading channels. Information theory concepts such as channel capacity and spectral efficiency are also mentioned. 
2. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking): The paper focuses on MIMO-OTFS, a communication system that combines the benefits of MIMO and OTFS. The paper discusses signal detection and channel estimation techniques for this system. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses a communication system and its components (modulation, signal detection, channel estimation) which can be viewed as a control system. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses a communication system and its performance in high-Doppler fading channels, which is relevant to wireless networking. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses a modulation technique (OTFS) that can be used for multimedia applications such as video streaming in high-Doppler fading channels.
